node.title: Why do humans need to eat many different kind of foods to get their vitamins etc but large animals like cows only need grass to survive?
Why can people walk many miles without discomfort, but when they stand for more than 15 minutes or so, they get uncomfortable?
How did we get to the point where laptops and smartphones are in the same price range?
How after 5000 years of humanity surviving off of bread do we have so many people within the last decade who are entirely allergic to gluten?
So how does the the human brain ignore the second the?
